0no%20matter%20what%2C%20he%20may%20decide%20he%20has%20little%20to%20lose%20by%20testifying%2C%20according%20to%20Sarah%20Krissoff%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20may%20at%20least%20be%20able%20to%20elicit%20a%20little%20sympathy%20from%20jurors%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20conviction%20seems%20almost%20inevitable%20based%20on%20what's%20presented%20in%20the%20courtroom%20so%20far%2C%20he%20has%20probably%20not%20that%20much%20to%20lose%20by%20testifying%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Krissoff%2C%20now%20a%20defense%20attorney%20at%20Cozen%20O'Connor.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20it%20does%20humanize%20him%20in%20a%20way%20to%20the%20jury%20that%20can%20be%20very%20effective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222223%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22sam%20bankman%20fried%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c1878d9440b7001926a969%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFTX%20founder%20Sam%20Bankman-Fried.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FMary%20Altaffer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20for%20Bankman-Fried's%20defense%20team%20is%20that%20they%20might%20not%20have%20anyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaplan%20refused%20to%20allow%20them%20to%20have%20their%20pick%20of%20expert%20witnesses%20testify.%20Court%20filings%20indicate%20they%20planned%20to%20suggest%20the%20norms%20of%20cryptocurrency%20exchanges%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20those%20operating%20outside%20of%20the%20US%2C%20as%20FTX%20was%20%E2%80%94%20may%20allow%20for%20the%20use%20of%20customer%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20those%20expert%20witnesses%2C%20Bankman-Fried's%20defense%20team%20has%20little%20scaffolding%20to%20support%20the%20closing%20arguments%20they'll%20present%20to%20jurors%2C%20according%20to%20Paul%20Tuchmann%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20Wiggin%20and%20Dana%2C%20and%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20for%20a%20number%20of%20reasons%20to%20have%20those%20witnesses%2C%20both%20because%20it%20gives%20the%20jury%20something%20to%20chew%20on%2C%20something%20to%20hang%20their%20hat%20on%2C%20and%20then%20by%20extension%20something%20for%20the%20defense%20to%20kind%20of%20point%20to%20in%20their%20closing%20arguments%2C%26quot%3B%20Tuchmann%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EProsecutors%20may%20have%20been%20preparing%20for%20SBF%20to%20testify%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20have%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20showing%20spreadsheets%20that%20demonstrate%20the%20behind-the-scenes%20financial%20relationship%20between%20FTX%20and%20Alameda%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20messages%20that%20directly%20point%20to%20how%20much%20Bankman-Fried%20knew%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20he%20knew%20it%20%E2%80%94%20are%20a%20little%20harder%20to%20come%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankman-Fried%20did%20much%20of%20his%20communicating%20on%20Signal%2C%20a%20messaging%20app.%20He%20told%20employees%20to%20use%20its%20auto-deletion%20features%2C%20according%20to%20witnesses%20who%20testified%20in%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20wasn't%20much%20benefit%20to%20keeping%20messages%20around%2C%20and%20if%20regulators%20found%20something%20they%20didn't%20like%20in%20those%20messages%2C%20that%20could%20be%20bad%20for%20the%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-trial-adam-yedidia-bug-8-billion-alameda-2023-10%5C%22%3Edeveloper%20Adam%20Yedidia%20testified%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20explaining%20Bankman-Fried's%20reasoning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20communication%20records%20shown%20at%20trial%20come%20from%20November%202022%2C%20when%20FTX%20was%20collapsing%20and%20those%20auto-deletion%20features%20were%20turned%20off%2C%20and%20in%20a%20smattering%20of%20screenshots%20taken%20by%20his%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Caroline%20Ellison%20courtroom%20sketch%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65259b6d68f1d46f52ad8c7c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECaroline%20Ellison%20testified%20in%20the%20trial%20of%20her%20ex-boyfriend%2C%20Sam%20Bankman-Fried%3Cp%3EJANE%20ROSENBERG%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20that%20reason%2C%20the%20case%20against%20Bankman-Fried%20rests%20on%20the%20credibility%20of%20his%20alleged%20co-conspirators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20cross-examining%20Ellison%2C%20Wang%2C%20and%20Singh%2C%20his%20defense%20attorneys%20have%20suggested%20that%20they're%20implicating%20Bankman-Fried%20only%20to%20seek%20a%20lighter%20prison%20sentence%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20least%20theoretically%2C%20the%20question%20isn't%20so%20much%20necessarily%2C%20'Is%20all%20of%20that%20wrong%3F'%20or%20'Is%20that%20stuff%20that%20they%20walk%20through%20in%20the%20spreadsheet%20criminal%3F'%26quot%3B%20Tuchmann%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20'Did%20SBF%20know%20about%20it%3F%20Did%20he%20direct%20them%20to%20do%20it%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20own%20questioning%20of%20the%20cooperating%20witnesses%2C%20prosecutors%20have%20encouraged%20them%20to%20be%20open%20about%20taking%20responsibility%20for%20their%20crimes.%20Wang%20forthrightly%20said%20that%20what%20he%20did%20was%20wrong.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaroline-ellison-freaked-out-alameda-owed-billions-lenders-2023-10%5C%22%3EEllison%20teared%20up%20on%20the%20witness%20stand%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20talking%20about%20the%20weight%20of%20her%20guilt.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-trial-nishad-singh-testimony-ftx-scam-going-2023-10%5C%22%3ESingh%20talked%20about%20how%20he%20became%20%26quot%3Bsuicidal%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20knowing%20he%20took%20money%20from%20customers%20and%20covering%20it%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20have%20also%20taken%20pains%20to%20suggest%20that%20Bankman-Fried%20is%20a%20serial%20liar.%20They%20pointed%20to%20his%20tweets%20around%20the%20time%20of%20the%20FTX%20collapse%20when%20he%20falsely%20said%20the%20company%20had%20enough%20liquidity%20to%20cover%20customer%20withdrawals.%20And%2C%20according%20to%20Ellison%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-hair-higher-bonuses-car-caroline-ellison-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBankman-Fried's%20unkempt%20hair%20and%20reputation%20for%20slovenliness%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20public%20relations.%20She%20testified%20that%20he%20had%20a%20luxury%20car%20before%20getting%20a%20Toyota%20Corolla%20because%20%26quot%3Bhe%20thought%20it%20was%20better%20for%20his%20image.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20witness%20stand%2C%20Ellison%20said%20Bankman-Fried%20told%20her%20that%2C%20under%20the%20effective%20altruism%20philosophy%20he%20subscribed%20to%2C%20it%20was%20OK%20to%20be%20dishonest%20because%20%26quot%3Brules%20like%20don't%20lie%20or%20don't%20steal%26quot%3B%20don't%20%26quot%3Bfit%20into%20that%20framework.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20said%20that%20he%20was%20a%20utilitarian%2C%20and%20he%20believed%20that%20the%20ways%20that%20people%20tried%20to%20justify%20rules%20like%20don't%20lie%20and%20don't%20steal%20within%20utilitarianism%20didn't%20work%2C%20and%20he%20thought%20that%20the%20only%20moral%20rule%20that%20mattered%20was%20doing%20whatever%20would%20maximize%20utility%2C%26quot%3B%20Ellison%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EProsecutors%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20judge%20%E2%80%94%20can%20use%20SBF's%20media%20interviews%20against%20him%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20prosecutors%20have%20the%20burden%20of%20proof%20in%20criminal%20cases%2C%20they%20often%20tell%20defendants%20not%20to%20testify.%20All%20they%20technically%20need%20to%20do%20is%20undercut%20the%20prosecution%2C%20not%20make%20any%20kind%20of%20affirmative%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%2C%20however%2C%20is%20ultimately%20up%20to%20the%20defendant%20himself.%20And%20Bankman-Fried's%20earlier%20interviews%20complicate%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20the%20sort%20of%20fortunate%20or%20unfortunate%20experience%20of%20having%20a%20lot%20of%20defendants%20testify.%20And%20there's%20a%20type%2C%26quot%3B%20Krissoff%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIn%20my%20view%2C%20there's%20often%20certain%20categories%20of%20defendants%20that%20like%20to%20testify.%20And%20in%20a%20white-collar%20case%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20when%20the%20person's%20veracity%20is%20what's%20at%20issue%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20the%20defendant%20to%20want%20to%20testify%20and%20in%20fact%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Bankman-Fried%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651d2c882ce014759e744416%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECourt%20sketch%20of%20Sam%20Bankman-Fried%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20his%20trial%3Cp%3EJANE%20ROSENBERG%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Bankman-Fried%20takes%20the%20stand%2C%20he'll%20be%20cross-examined%20by%20prosecutors.%20And%20those%20prosecutors%20have%20plenty%20of%20material%20to%20try%20to%20catch%20him%20in%20a%20lie.%20He's%20testified%20before%20Congress%20and%20given%20numerous%20interviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%20on%20Thursday%2C%20prosecutors%20pulled%20up%20a%20video%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2F0Hxf4Vf54PI%3Fsi%3DXcR2SBJNAZygTrfb%26t%3D317%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20interview%20Bankman-Fried%20gave%20to%20ABC%20News%20in%20December%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20days%20before%20he%20was%20extradited%2C%20where%20he%20squirmed%20when%20asked%20direct%20questions%20about%20what%20he%20knew%20and%20when.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20hesitated%20and%20hedged%20extensively%2C%20saying%20he%20was%20only%20%26quot%3Bvaguely%20aware%26quot%3B%20that%20FTX%20deposits%20were%20being%20funneled%20to%20Alameda.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20months%20later%2C%20that%20wouldn't%20seem%20to%20be%20the%20case%2C%20according%20to%20testimony%20given%20by%20his%20former%20executives%20who%20have%20testified%20against%20him.%20If%20Bankman-Fried%20takes%20the%20stand%2C%20prosecutors%20will%20almost%20certainly%20point%20to%20more%20material%20and%20catch%20him%20in%20any%20contradictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20particularly%20complicated%20for%20him%20because%20of%20how%20much%20he's%20talked%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Krissoff%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20he's%20going%20to%20have%20to%20weave%20a%20story%20together%20that%20both%20takes%20into%20account%20all%20of%20the%20evidence%20that's%20presented%20in%20the%20government's%20weeks%20of%20presentation%20and%20also%20all%20of%20the%20statements%20he%20made%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20even%20bigger%20issue%20for%20Bankman-Fried%20could%20be%20Kaplan's%20future%20sentencing%2C%20if%20he's%20found%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%20proceedings%2C%20Kaplan%20has%20shown%20little%20sympathy%20for%20Bankman-Fried.%20Over%20the%20summer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-bail-revoked-jail-alleged-witness-tampering-2023-8%5C%22%3Ehe%20jailed%20Bankman-Fried%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20finding%20that%20he%20tried%20to%20tamper%20with%20two%20witnesses%20ahead%20of%20trial%20and%20repeatedly%20violated%20the%20terms%20of%20his%20home%20confinement.%20And%20that%20was%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprosecutors-send-sam-bankman-fried-jail-for-witness-tampering-2023-7%5C%22%3Eexpressing%20exasperation%20in%20several%20earlier%20hearings%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20prosecutors%20didn't%20seek%20more%20stringent%20restrictions%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Kaplan%20finds%20that%2C%20on%20top%20of%20everything%2C%20Bankman-Fried%20lied%20on%20the%20witness%20stand%2C%20he%20could%20issue%20a%20much%20tougher%20sentence%20%E2%80%94%20not%20to%20mention%20add%20complications%20to%20a%20second%20criminal%20trial%20on%20campaign%20finance%20charges%2C%20scheduled%20for%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20may%20make%20the%20calculation%20of%2C%20'You%20know%20what%2C%20if%20I%20get%20convicted%2C%20Judge%20Kaplan's%20going%20to%20sentence%20me%20into%20next%20century%20anyway%2C%20so%20I%20might%20as%20well%20testify%20in%20an%20effort%20of%20avoiding%20that%2C'%26quot%3B%20Tuchmann%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20risky%20because%20maybe%20that's%20not%20what%20Judge%20Kaplan%20would%20do.%20But%20if%20he%20sees%20SBF%20testify%20on%20the%20stand%20then%20in%20a%20way%20that%20he%20believes%20is%20untruthful%2C%20then%20maybe%20he%20would%20tack%20on%20additional%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-trial-will-sbf-testify-witness-defense-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697748990000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65172e4e846a2f0019a119c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-trial-will-sbf-testify-witness-defense-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sam%20Bankman-Fried%20needs%20to%20decide%20soon%20whether%20he'll%20take%20the%20stand%20in%20his%20criminal%20trial%20in%20Manhattan%20federal%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jshamsian%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Shamsian%2CKatie%20Balevic)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-bankman-fried-trial-will-sbf-testify-witness-defense-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22DJ%20Mark%20the%2045%20King%2C%20Produc