2%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fjerome-powell-federal-reserve-treasury-bond-market-collapse-yields-debt-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Can%20hydrogen%20be%20green%3F%20The%20debate%20heats%20up%20as%20the%20White%20House%20pours%20%247%20billion%20into%20hydrogen%20hubs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Round%20white%20storage%20tanks%20at%20China's%20first%20first%20solar-powered%20green%20hydrogen%20pilot%20project%20in%20Xinjiang.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653147f7be9edfa8eda4bc44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22545%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStorage%20tanks%20at%20China's%20first%20first%20solar-powered%20green%20hydrogen%20pilot%20project%20in%20Xinjiang.%3Cp%3EVCG%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHydrogen%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20a%20climate%20solution%2C%20but%20right%20now%20it's%20a%20dirty%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20White%20House%20is%20spending%20%247%20billion%20to%20spur%C2%A0%26quot%3Bclean%26quot%3B%20hydrogen.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20climate%20advocates%2C%20scientists%20worry%20that%20fossil-fuel%20companies%20will%20cash%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20article%20is%20part%20of%20Insider's%20weekly%20newsletter%20on%20sustainability.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Finsider-sustainability%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESign%20up%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20us%20probably%20think%20of%20hydrogen%20in%20terms%20of%20H2O%20%E2%80%94%20the%20water%20we%20drink%2C%20bathe%20in%2C%20and%20cook%20with%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20help%20build%20a%20low-carbon%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F10%2F13%2Fbiden-harris-administration-announces-regional-clean-hydrogen-hubs-to-drive-clean-manufacturing-and-jobs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eis%20pouring%20up%20to%20%247%20billion%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20seven%20hydrogen%20hubs%20in%20regions%20including%20the%20Gulf%20Coast%2C%20Pacific%20Northwest%2C%20and%20Appalachia.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20spur%20the%20production%20of%20%26quot%3Bclean%26quot%3B%20hydrogen%2C%20because%20the%20way%20it's%20currently%20produced%20is%20a%20dirty%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20hydrogen%20is%20separated%20from%20methane%20in%20natural%20gas%20through%20an%20energy-intensive%20process%20that%20produces%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20responsible%20for%20warming%20the%20planet.%20Hydrogen%20is%20mainly%20used%20to%20refine%20oil%20and%20make%20chemical%20fertilizers%2C%20but%20experts%20say%20it%20can%20also%20be%20used%20for%20energy%20storage%20and%20as%20a%20fuel%20for%20long-haul%20trucks%20and%20airplanes.%20If%20the%20production%20process%20is%20cleaned%20up%2C%20it%20could%20help%20decarbonize%20industries%20that%20use%20hydrogen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20with%20so%20many%20climate%20solutions%2C%20there's%20a%20debate%20over%20the%20best%20path%20forward.%20It%20boils%20down%20to%20this%3A%20Should%20hydrogen%20continue%20to%20be%20made%20from%20natural%20gas%20but%20paired%20with%20carbon-capture%20technology%20and%20storage%3F%20This%20is%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bblue%26quot%3B%20hydrogen.%20Or%20should%20it%20be%20made%20from%20a%20renewable-energy%20powered%20process%20known%20as%20electrolysis%2C%20which%20splits%20water%20into%20hydrogen%20and%20oxygen%3F%20This%20is%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bgreen%26quot%3B%20hydrogen%20%E2%80%94%20an%20approach%20favored%20by%20many%20climate%20advocates.%20Both%20are%20still%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20said%20about%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20overall%20investment%20in%20hydrogen%20hubs%20will%20be%20associated%20with%20the%20green%20kind.%20That%20still%20didn't%20land%20well%20with%20some%20climate%20advocates%20and%20scientists%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1002%2Fese3.956%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecite%20research%20suggesting%20that%20blue%20hydrogen%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20clean%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20a%20scam%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Howarth%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20ecology%20and%20environmental%20biology%20at%20Cornell%20University%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20use%20that%20word%20lightly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowarth%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1002%2Fese3.956%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethat%20blue%20hydrogen%20requires%20more%20natural%20gas%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20therefore%20produces%20more%20methane%20emissions.%20That's%20concerning%20because%20methane%20heats%20up%20the%20planet%2080%20times%20faster%20than%20carbon%20dioxide%20over%20a%20two-decade%20period%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20energy%20to%20capture%20the%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20and%20that%20comes%20from%20burning%20even%20more%20natural%20gas%2C%26quot%3B%20Howarth%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20not%20a%20surprise%20to%20me%20that%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry%20likes%20the%20idea%20of%20blue%20hydrogen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Clean%20Air%20Task%20Force%2C%20an%20environmental%20nonprofit%20that's%20working%20with%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Energy%2C%20hydrogen-hub%20project%20developers%2C%20and%20community-based%20groups%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20they%20also%20support%20the%20White%20House's%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnna%20Menke%2C%20the%20task%20force's%20senior%20hydrogen-hubs%20manager%2C%20said%20she%20wants%20the%20debate%20to%20move%20away%20from%20green%20versus%20blue%20hydrogen%20because%20each%20technology%20has%20its%20pros%20and%20cons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreen%20hydrogen%20is%20more%20expensive%20and%20could%20lead%20to%20more%20emissions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiopscience.iop.org%2Farticle%2F10.1088%2F1748-9326%2Facacb5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethan%20its%20conventional%20version%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20electrolyzers%20aren't%20powered%20by%20additional%20renewable%20energy%20on%20the%20grid%2C%20Menke%20said.%20She%20acknowledged%20that%20for%20blue%20hydrogen%20to%20truly%20be%20a%20climate%20solution%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20must%20reduce%20methane%20leaks%20in%20their%20infrastructures%20and%20develop%20carbon-capture%20systems%20that%20trap%20a%20lot%20of%20emissions%20and%20store%20them%20permanently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.rsc.org%2Fen%2Fcontent%2Farticlelanding%2F2022%2Fse%2Fd1se01508g%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%20to%20US%20and%20European%20researchers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHydrogen%20hub%20projects%20that%20applied%20for%20federal%20funding%20had%20to%20meet%20a%20range%20of%20criteria%2C%20including%20low%20emissions%20targets%2C%20Brian%20Korgel%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Energy%20Institute%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%2C%20told%20Insider.%20Korgel%20is%20working%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hyvelocityhub.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHyVelocity%20Hub%20along%20the%20Gulf%20Coast%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20awarded%20%241.2%20billion%20by%20the%20Biden%20administration%20and%20is%20led%20by%20companies%20including%20Chevron%2C%20ExxonMobil%2C%20and%20Sempra%20Infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20project%20aims%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20both%20blue%20and%20green%20hydrogen%20can%20be%20made%20with%20low%20emissions%20at%20a%20competitive%20cost%2C%20while%20creating%20jobs%20and%20other%20benefits%20for%20disadvantaged%20communities.%20Korgel's%20team%20at%20the%20Energy%20Institute%20is%20conducting%20environmental%20and%20economic%20analyses%20of%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20some%20safeguards%2C%26quot%3B%20Korgel%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20projects%20have%20to%20meet%20emissions%20standards%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20in%20companies'%20benefit%20to%20do%20the%20smoke%20and%20mirrors%20thing%20because%20they%20won't%20get%20the%20grant%20money%2C%20which%20ratchets%20up%20over%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKorgel%20noted%20that%20the%20federal%20definition%20of%20%26quot%3Bclean%26quot%3B%20hydrogen%20has%20been%20evolving%2C%20but%20should%20be%20more%20clear%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20unlikely%20government%20agency%20could%20settle%20the%20debate.%20The%20Internal%20Revenue%20Service%20has%20to%20decide%20what%20%26quot%3Bclean%26quot%3B%20hydrogen%20is%20eligible%20for%20a%20tax%20credit%20worth%20up%20to%20an%20estimated%20%24100%20billion%20over%20its%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhydrogen-energy-help-climate-crisis-but-still-hurdles-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697744928000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65316402be9edfa8eda4f79a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhydrogen-energy-help-climate-crisis-but-still-hurdles-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hydrogen%20energy%20could%20help%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20President%20Biden%20is%20pouring%20up%20to%20%247%20billion%20into%20hydrogen%20hubs%20around%20the%20country.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20spur%20production%20of%20%26quot%3Bclean%26quot%3B%20hydrogen.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudreau%40insider.com%20(Catherine%20Boudreau)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhydrogen-energy-help-climate-crisis-but-still-hurdles