article%2F2022-07%2F19%2Ffull%2F1658243055-3588.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgo-first-extends-flight-cancellation-till-nov-30-citing-operational-reasons-123101901159_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20airline%20has%20approximately%204%2C200%20employees%2C%20and%20it%20reported%20total%20revenue%20from%20operations%20at%20Rs%204%2C183%20crore%20in%20the%20financial%20year%202021-22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgo-first-extends-flight-cancellation-till-nov-30-citing-operational-reasons-123101901159_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgo-first-extends-flight-cancellation-till-nov-30-citing-operational-reasons-123101901159_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgo-first-extends-flight-cancellation-till-nov-30-citing-operational-reasons-123101901159_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Court%20to%20ED%3A%20Can%20Issue%20Summons%20Under%20Section%2050%20of%20PMLA%2C%20but%20Cannot%20Make%20Arrests%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F29142658%2F5606166528_b12b9c251a_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Any%20summons%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20issues%20under%20Section%2050%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%2C%202002%20(PMLA)%20does%20not%20naturally%20result%20in%20power%20to%20arrest%20someone%2C%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20said%20on%20Thursday%20(October%2019).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20single-judge%20bench%20comprising%20Justice%20Anup%20Jairam%20Bhambhani%20clarified%20that%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20arrest%20someone%20falls%20under%20a%20different%20section%20of%20the%20PMLA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20power%20under%20section%2050%20of%20the%20PMLA%20to%20issue%20summons%20to%20a%20person%20and%20to%20require%20the%20production%20of%20documents%20and%20record%20statements%2C%20which%20is%20akin%20to%20the%20powers%20of%20a%20civil%20court%2C%20is%20different%20and%20distinct%20from%20the%20power%20under%20section%2019%20to%20arrest%20a%20person%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20231019135146%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fjudgementphp-499349.pdf%5C%22%3Ethe%20judgment%20issued%20by%20Justice%20Bhambhani%3C%2Fa%3E%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20power%20to%20arrest%20does%20not%20reside%20in%20section%2050%20nor%20does%20it%20arise%20as%20a%20natural%20corollary%20of%20summons%20issued%20under%20section%2050%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20judgment%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20added%20that%20the%20ED%20cannot%20be%20restrained%20from%20exercising%20its%20power%20to%20issue%20summons%20on%20the%20apprehension%20that%20its%20doing%20so%20may%20lead%20it%20to%20arrest%20someone%2C%20and%20vice%20versa.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20that%20is%20permitted%2C%20any%20and%20every%20person%20summonsed%20%5Bsic%5D%20under%20section%2050%20of%20the%20PMLA%2C%20to%20produce%20documents%20or%20give%20a%20statement%20on%20oath%2C%20could%20resist%20such%20summons%20expressing%20mere%20apprehension%20that%20he%20may%20face%20arrest%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20ED%2C%20in%20exercise%20of%20the%20powers%20under%20section%2019%20of%20the%20PMLA%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20a%20position%20would%20be%20antithetic%20to%20the%20statutory%20scheme.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20court%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20the%20authorities%20could%20not%20use%20section%2019%20of%20the%20PMLA%20to%20arrest%20someone%20%E2%80%9Con%20their%20whims%20and%20fancies%E2%80%9D%20and%20must%20meet%20three%20requirements%20before%20making%20an%20arrest%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFirstly%2C%20the%20Director%20must%20entertain%20a%20reasonable%20belief%20that%20the%20person%20arrested%20is%20guilty%20of%20an%20offence%20under%20the%20PMLA%2C%20and%20not%20under%20any%20other%20enactment%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20the%20reasons%20for%20such%20belief%20must%20be%20recorded%20in%20writing%3B%20and%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20such%20belief%20must%20be%20based%20on%20material%20that%20is%20in%20the%20Director%E2%80%99s%20possession.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-the-enforcement-directorate-has-become-an-excessive-directorate%5C%22%3EHow%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20Has%20Become%20an%20Excessive%20Directorate%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20section%2019%20of%20the%20PMLA%20requires%20the%20ED%20to%20inform%20the%20accused%20of%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpankaj-bansal-verdict-valuable-step-basic-procedural-rights-applicable-ed%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20written%20format%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENon-compliance%20with%20this%20requirement%20vitiates%20an%20arrest%2C%20and%20entitles%20the%20accused%20to%20be%20set%20free%20unconditionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Bhambhani%20of%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20also%20noted%20in%20his%20judgement%20yesterday%20that%20non-compliance%20with%20section%2019(1)%20of%20the%20PMLA%20vitiates%20an%20arrest%20and%20that%20compliance%20with%20section%2019(2)%20%E2%80%9Cis%20a%20solemn%20function%20which%20brooks%20no%20exceptions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20was%20hearing%20a%20plea%20by%20Ashish%20Mittal%20to%20quash%20a%202020%20ECIR%20(enforcement%20case%20information%20report%2C%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20version%20of%20an%20FIR)%20related%20to%20the%20affairs%20of%20a%20company%20named%20Educomp%20Solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMittal%20said%20he%20was%20apprehensive%20that%20the%20ED%20would%20%E2%80%98illegally%20arrest%E2%80%99%20him%20and%20that%20he%20would%20be%20made%20a%20scapegoat%20in%20the%20case%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20court%20said%20that%20as%20Mittal%20was%20not%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20case%20the%20ED%20may%20not%20subject%20him%20to%20coercive%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ED%20is%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20financial%20crimes%20investigation%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%20the%20ED%20has%20been%20granted%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftracking-the-ed-case-by-case-puzzling-questions-emerge-in-its-handling-of-opposition-leaders%5C%22%3Eextraordinary%20powers%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20amendments%20to%20the%20PMLA%2C%20which%20critics%20say%20allows%20the%20agency%20to%20be%20misused%20to%20target%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20political%20opponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fsupreme-court-pmla-validity-enforcement-directorate-8054053%2F%5C%22%3Eupheld%20key%20provisions%20of%20the%20PMLA%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIts%20judgement%20was%20highly%20controversial%20in%20view%20of%20its%20adverse%20effects%20on%20citizens%E2%80%99%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20special%20bench%20of%20the%20top%20court%20on%20Wednesday%20(October%2018)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Freconsidering-pmla-judgment-sc-asserts-its-power-to-refer-it-to-a-larger-bench%5C%22%3Eappeared%20inclined%20to%20consider%20arguments%20in%20favour%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20referring%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20July%202022%20judgement%20to%20a%20constitution%20bench%20of%20five%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697732432000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F29142658%