20September%2C%20chief%20metropolitan%20magistrate%20Siddhartha%20Malik%20of%20the%20Tis%20Hazari%20courts%20ruled%20that%20there%20were%20no%20reasonable%20grounds%20for%20the%20police%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20the%20devices%20since%20the%20investigating%20officer%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fnews%2Fdelhi-court-orders-police-to-return-devices-seized-from-the-wires-editors%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehad%20possession%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20them%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%20and%20the%20court%20had%20been%20told%20that%20the%20Forensic%20Science%20Lab%20had%20already%20taken%20mirror%20images%20for%20further%20investigation.%20The%20police%E2%80%99s%20argument%20that%20the%20devices%20might%20be%20needed%20again%20for%20subsequent%20investigation%20is%20%E2%80%9Cspeculative%20in%20nature%20based%20on%20the%20presumption%20of%20coming%20to%20light%20some%20new%20fact%20at%20a%20later%20stage%2C%20which%20may%20or%20may%20not%20happen%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20magistrate%20had%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20devices%20cannot%20be%20kept%20indefinitely%20by%20the%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20represented%20in%20court%20by%20Ashwath%20Sitaraman%2C%20Prasanna%20S.%20and%20Archit%20Krishna.%20The%20devices%20were%20seized%20by%20the%20police%20in%20October%202022%20following%20a%20complaint%20against%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20a%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20magistrate%E2%80%99s%20order%20was%20appealed%20by%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20before%20the%20additional%20sessions%20court.%20After%20hearing%20the%20arguments%2C%20judge%20Rajawat%20said%20that%20the%20press%20is%20the%20fourth%20pillar%20of%20democracy%20and%20%E2%80%9Cif%20it%20is%20not%20allowed%20to%20function%20and%20operate%20independently%2C%20it%20would%20cause%20serious%20injury%20to%20the%20foundations%20of%20our%20democracy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6continuous%20seizure%20of%20electronic%20devices%20of%20the%20respondents%2C%20is%20not%20only%20causing%20undue%20hardship%20to%20them%2C%20but%20impinges%20upon%20their%20fundamental%20right%20of%20Freedom%20of%20profession%2C%20occupation%2C%20trade%20or%20business%20as%20guaranteed%20under%20Article%2019(1)(g)%20as%20well%20as%20Freedom%20of%20Speech%20and%20expression%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20as%20admittedly%20the%20respondents%20are%20working%20for%20news%20portal%20The%20Wire%20which%20is%20engaged%20in%20disseminating%20news%20and%20information%20and%20the%20electronic%20devices%20were%20being%20used%20for%20their%20work.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJudge%20Rajawat%20noted%20that%20the%20chief%20metropolitan%20magistrate%E2%80%99s%20order%20not%20only%20safeguarded%20the%20interest%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20employees%20but%20also%20ensured%20that%20they%20are%20duty%20bound%20to%20keep%20the%20devices%20safe%20from%20tampering%20and%20if%20they%20notice%20any%20anomaly%20with%20the%20devices%2C%20they%20should%20immediately%20notify%20the%20investigating%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20noted%20that%20Section%20457%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20(CrPC)%20enables%20the%20court%20to%20decide%20the%20custody%20of%20property%20pending%20investigation%20and%20cited%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20in%20%3Cem%3EBasava%20Kom%20Dyamangouda%20Patil%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1977)%20to%20say%20that%20the%20police%20should%20not%20indefinitely%20keep%20property%20in%20its%20custody.%20The%20same%20verdict%20said%20that%20the%20court%20needs%20to%20determine%20if%20the%20property%20seized%20by%20the%20police%20is%20required%20in%20the%20future%20course%20of%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESection%20451%20of%20the%20CrPC%2C%20judge%20Rajawat%20noted%2C%20gives%20the%20court%20wide%20discretion%20to%20make%20orders%20for%20proper%20custody%20of%20the%20property%20pending%20trial.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20process%20the%20Court%20may%20incidentally%20be%20guided%20by%20the%20consideration%20as%20to%20who%20is%20the%20person%20prima%20facie%20entitled%20to%20the%20possession%20of%20the%20case%20property%20and%20hand%20over%20its%20possession%20to%20him%20with%20a%20view%20to%20safeguard%20his%20interest%20but%20that%20may%20not%20be%20the%20sole%20consideration%20for%20the%20Court%20while%20entrusting%20custody%20of%20the%20case%20property%20or%20property%20used%20in%20the%20commission%20of%20an%20offence%20etc.%20to%20any%20of%20the%20rival%20claimants%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20order%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697724394000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05100450%2Fsignal-2023-10-03-154153_002-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdevice-journalists-seized-press-freedom-delhi-court-the-wire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20observation%20was%20made%20by%20additional%20sessions%20judge%20Pawan%20Singh%20Rajawat%20while%20upholding%20a%20previous%20order%20asking%20the%20Delhi%20police%20to%20release%20devices%20seized%20from%20The%20Wire's%20employees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdevice-journalists-seized-press-freedom-delhi-court-the-wire%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Miami%20dentist%20fired%20for%20removing%20Israeli%20hostages%E2%80%99%20posters%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697724162000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104559993%2Cimgsize-105232.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fmiami-dentist-fired-for-removing-israeli-hostages-posters%2Farticleshow%2F104559923.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22le