0toward%20a%20concrete%20jungle.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWithin%20the%20labyrinth%20of%20Kumhar%20Gram%20(potter%E2%80%99s%20colony)%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Uttam%20Nagar%2C%20more%20than%20700%20families%20work%20relentlessly%20to%20put%20forward%20the%20finest%20terracotta%20products%20for%20a%20public%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20realise%20the%20genius%20behind%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20field%20researchers%2C%20as%20part%20of%20an%20ethnographic%20project%20undertaken%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvisualstoryboardscnes.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVisual%20Storyboard%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20team%2C%20tried%20to%20interact%20with%20the%20masters%2C%20craftsperson%2C%20and%20entrepreneurs%C2%A0%20of%20Uttam%20Nagar%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%20potter%20colony.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecolony%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0has%20been%20home%20to%20its%20potters%20since%20the%20late%201960s%20when%20the%20community%20migrated%20from%20Alwar%20%E2%80%93%20known%20for%20its%20traditions%20and%20palaces%20%E2%80%93%20to%20the%20urban%20enclave%20of%20Uttam%20Nagar.%20It%20was%20the%20existential%20need%20to%20combat%20unemployment%20and%20poverty%20that%20triggered%20their%20move%20to%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20village%2C%20now%20adorned%20with%20statues%20of%20revered%20gods%2C%20was%20merely%20a%20piece%20of%20land%20when%20the%20potters%20first%20arrived.%20They%20converted%20the%20barren%20land%20into%20a%20settlement%20that%20eventually%20became%20a%20hub%20for%20handcrafted%20earthenware.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20286px)%2085vw%2C%20286px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19145519%2FScreenshot-2023-10-19-at-2.50.27-PM-226x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22286%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19145519%2FScreenshot-2023-10-19-at-2.50.27-PM-226x300.png%20226w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19145519%2FScreenshot-2023-10-19-at-2.50.27-PM-771x1024.png%20771w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19145519%2FScreenshot-2023-10-19-at-2.50.27-PM.png%20878w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680821%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22380%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20resident%20of%20the%20potter%20colony.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20seen%20their%20fathers%20and%20grandfathers%20be%20involved%20in%20the%20craft%2C%20third%20and%20fourth-generation%20potters%20diligently%20labour%20their%20days%20away%20to%20expand%20their%20business%20further.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20been%20a%20silent%20observer%20of%20my%20father%20and%20the%20neighbours%20immersing%20themselves%20deeply%20into%20pottery%20and%20the%20close-knit%20community%20that%20revolves%20around%20it%20since%20as%20far%20as%20I%20can%20remember.%20Gradually%2C%20I%20picked%20up%20the%20craft%20from%20them.%20I%20tried%20my%20hand%20at%20corporate%20jobs%20after%20graduating%C2%A0%20but%20it%20did%20not%20bode%20well%20for%20me.%20The%20craft%20of%20pottery%20gives%20me%20more%20comfort%20and%20joy%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Rakesh%20Kumar%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20the%20potter%E2%80%99s%20colony.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20we%20moved%20away%20from%20the%20main%20street%20%E2%80%93%20filled%20with%20stalls%20and%20shops%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20towards%20the%20narrow%20alleyways%2C%20we%20observed%20the%20actual%20life%20of%20the%20colony.%20It%20is%20in%20these%20alleyways%20that%20one%20gets%20to%C2%A0%20see%20the%20entire%20process%20behind%20the%20craft.%20It%20starts%20with%20the%20mound%20of%20clay%20in%20front%20of%20every%20house%2C%20usually%20sourced%20from%20Haryana.%20Naturally%2C%20this%20clay%20is%20impure%20and%20requires%20sieving%20to%20remove%20pebbles%20and%20dust%20particles%20that%20hinder%20the%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%20the%20impurities%20are%20removed%20water%20is%20meticulously%20incorporated%20into%20the%20clay%2C%20transforming%20its%20coarse%20texture%20into%20a%20more%20pliable%20form%2C%20making%20it%20ready%20for%20further%20processing.%20This%20is%20the%20clay%20that%20is%20thrown%20onto%20the%20wheel%20to%20give%20it%20shape.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20wheel%20head%20rotates%20at%20a%20steady%20pace%2C%20artisans%E2%80%99%20hands%20work%20to%20shape%20the%20clay%20in%20a%20desired%20form.%20After%20using%20an%20array%20of%20tools%20to%20change%20the%20design%20of%20their%20products%2C%20artisans%20leave%20them%20alone%20to%20dry%20naturally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhandicraft-sector-government-policy-odds-security%5C%22%3EThe%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20Policies%20for%20Handicraft%20Sector%20Are%20at%20Odds%20With%20What%20It%20Endorses%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETypically%2C%20it%20takes%20a%20few%20days%20for%20the%20terracotta%20to%20dry%20and%20for%20the%20potters%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20more%20enjoyable%20phase%20of%20the%20process%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Once%20the%20product%20is%20dried%2C%20it%20goes%20into%20the%20kilns%20for%20baking.%20Sawdust%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eburadda%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20most%20commonly%20used%20for%20fueling%20these%20kilns%20to%20reach%20the%20desired%20temperature.%20The%20right%20mix%20of%20air%20and%20heat%20in%20the%20kilns%20completes%20this%20stage%20of%20the%20production%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20concluding%20step%20is%20the%20several%20rounds%20of%20detailing%20that%20takes%20place%2C%20usually%20through%20hand%20work%20or%20colouring.%20It%20is%20this%20stage%20of%20the%20process%20that%20sets%20all%20the%20artisans%20apart.%20No%20matter%20what%20type%20of%C2%A0%20product%20it%20may%20be%2C%20you%20will%20never%20find%20two%20pieces%20similar%20to%20each%20other%20in%20the%20Kumhar%20Gram.%20Once%20painted%20and%20designed%2C%20the%20products%20are%20left%20to%20dry%20once%20again%2C%20bringing%20us%20to%20an%20end%20of%20the%20production.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInspired%20by%20the%20rich%20tapestry%20of%20Rajasthan%E2%80%99s%20culture%2C%20these%20meticulously%20crafted%20products%20are%20embellished%20with%20the%20intricate%20designs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENevertheless%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20disheartening%20to%20observe%20that%20the%20largest%20pottery%20community%20in%20India%20has%20yielded%20to%20market%20forces%2C%20transforming%20from%20a%20tradition%20into%20a%20commercial%20endeavour.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20I%20rarely%20visit%20Rajasthan%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20our%20designs%20are%20inspired%20by%20the%20art%20and%20culture%20there.%20All%20of%20the%20simplistic%20and%20minimalistic%20designs%20that%20you%20see%20here%20have%20been%20deeply%20influenced%20by%20Alwar.%20It%20is%20very%20demoralising%20to%20see%20these%20designs%20being%20overshadowed%20by%20the%20flashy%2Fattractive%20items%20demanded%20by%20the%20customers%2C%E2%80%9D%20observes%20Niranjan%20Singh%20Prajapati.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19150120%2FScreenshot-2023-10-19-at-2.50.06-PM.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221097%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19150120%2FScreenshot-2023-10-19-at-2.50.06-PM.jpg%201097w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19150120%2FScreenshot-2023-10-19-at-2.50.06-PM-300x223.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19150120%2FScreenshot-2023-10-19-at-2.50.06-PM-1024x762.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-680825%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22816%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EClay%20pots%20drying%20before%20being%20sent%20to%20the%20kilns.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Indian%20art%20critic%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.openedition.org%2Fsamaj%2F3725%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGeeta%20Kapur%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Ctradition%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cmodernity%E2%80%9D%20are%20used%20as%20metaphors%20in%20decolonisation-related%20cultural%20conflicts%20in%20debates%20about%20the%20third%20world.%20When%20used%20to%20describe%20India%20and%20the%20developing%20world%2C%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Ctradition%E2%80%9D%20does%20not%20imply%20an%20impersonal%20heritage.%20The%20Indian%20handicraft%20industry%2C%20which%20makes%20up%20a%20sizeable%20portion%20of%20the%20decentralised%20sector%20of%20the%20economy%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F283009715_INDIAN_HANDICRAFT_GLOBALIZATION_IN_CONTEXT_OF_EXPORT%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIndian%2520folk%2520art%2520and%2520crafts%2Care%2520showing%2520a%2520growing%2520trend.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehas%20seen%20impressive%20growth%20in%20exports%2C%20makes%20this%20abundantly%20evident.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20local%20consumers%20continue%20to%20request%20new%20patterns%20and%20are%20reluctant%20to%20purchase%20classic%20themes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20cost%20of%20production%20being%20at%20an%20all-time%20high%2C%20the%20potters%20earn%20a%20profit%20of%20no%20more%20than%20Rs%202%20per%20product.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20clay%20that%20we%20get%20from%20Haryana%20was%20sold%20at%20a%20rate%20of%20Rs%201000.%20It%20now%20has%20reached%20Rs%204500%20just%20within%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20mentioned%20Narayani%20Devi%2C%20whose%20entire%20family%20works%20to%20produce%20flower%20pots%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enazarbattus%20(evil%20eyes)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWith%20the%20mud%20that%20costs%20us%20Rs%204500%2C%20we%20are%20barely%20able%20to%20fill%20one%20of%20our%20kilns.%20So%2C%20with%20more%20cost%20and%20less%20return%2C%20we%20barely%20make%20enough%20profits%20to%20live%2C%20let%20alone%20save.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20minuscule%20profits%2C%20along%20with%20long%20working%20hours%20suggest%20a%20bleak%20future%20for%20this%20exquisite%20craft.%20The%20younger%20generations%20feel%20alienated%20from%20the%20community%2C%20which%20is%20further%20encouraged%20by%20the%20parents%20who%E2%80%99d%20rather%20have%20them%20get%20a%20more%20stable%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBeing%20involved%20in%20pottery%20for%20the%20past%2018%20years%20has%20taught%20me%20a%20lot.%20One%20of%20the%20things%20is%20that%20this%20is%20not%20the%20future%20I%20wish%20for%20my%20children.%20I%20am%20stuck%20here%2C%20but%20I%20would%20rather%20have%20my%20daughters%20study%20and%20get%20a%20stable%20job%20than%20be%20stuck%20in%20this%20one-bedroom%20house%20with%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20Reena%20Kumar%20commented.%20In%20our%20next%20article%20in%20this%20two-part%20series%2C%20our%20objective%20is%20to%20delve%20deeper%20into%20the%20myriad%20challenges%20faced%20by%20these%20cultural%20stalwarts%2C%20as%20well%20as%20explore%20the%20assistance%20and%20support%20extended%20to%20them%20by%20governmental%20authorities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20these%20challenges%2C%20the%20community%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20their%20craft%20remains%20unwavering%2C%20and%20the%20artistic%20diversity%20among%20them%20ensures%20that%20each%20creation%20is%20a%20masterpiece%20in%20its%20own%20right.%20Their%20hands%20continue%20to%20serve%20their%20craft%20to%20wholesalers%20at%20a%20suboptimal%20price%2C%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20living%20for%20themselves%20and%20their%20families.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20of%20a%20two-part%20article%20series%20from%20CNES%E2%80%99%20Visual%20Storyboard%20team%20from%20a%20field%20project%20focusing%20on%20the%20lives-livelihoods%20of%20West%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20pottery%20makers%20and%20their%20endangered%20craft.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3ETavleen%20Kaur%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20Senior%20Research%20Assistant%20and%20Team%20Lead%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESwabhimaan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EVisual%20Storyboard%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20initiatives%20with%20CNES.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Director%2C%20CNES.%20He%20is%20currently%20an%20Honorary%20Research%20Fellow%20with%20Birkbeck%20College%2C%20University%20of%20London%20and%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20at%20School%20of%20International%20Development%20and%20Global%20Studies%2C%20University%20of%20Ottawa%2C%20Canada.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3EAnousha%20Singh%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20Research%20Intern%20with%20CNES%20and%20a%20student%20of%20Delhi%20University%E2%80%99s%20Ramanujan%20College.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697715000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19145419%2FScreenshot-2023-10-19-at-2.49.40-PM