%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kheda%20Public%20Flogging%3A%20Gujarat%20HC%20Awards%20Cops%2014-Day%20Jail%2C%20Stays%20Verdict%20for%203%20Months%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F05083127%2FScreenshot-2022-10-05-at-8.31.22-AM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20the%20Kheda%20public%20flogging%20case%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%20has%20sentenced%20four%20of%20the%20accused%20policemen%20to%2014%20days%20imprisonment%20and%20fined%20Rs%202%2C000%20each.%20However%2C%20the%20verdict%20has%20been%20stayed%20for%20three%20months%2C%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20cops%20to%20allow%20them%20to%20appeal%20against%20the%20judgement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fkheda-flogging-cops-14-days-prision-verdict-stayed-8990335%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20division%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20A.S.%20Supehia%20and%20Justice%20Gita%20Gopi%20described%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20October%2018%2C%20during%20the%20pronouncement%20of%20the%20verdict%20termed%20the%20incident%20%E2%80%9Cinhumane%E2%80%9D%20and%20an%20%E2%80%9Cact%20against%20humanity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20policemen%20in%20question%20were%20accused%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fgujarat-election-kheda-public-flogging-hindu-muslim-communalism%5C%22%3Epublicly%20flogging%3C%2Fa%3E%20five%20Muslim%20men%20by%20tying%20them%20to%20a%20pole%20following%20their%20arrest%20on%20October%204%20last%20year.%20The%20arrested%20had%20been%20accused%20of%20pelting%20stones%20at%20a%20garba%20event%20during%20the%20Navaratri%20festival%20the%20previous%20day%20in%20Undhela%20village%20in%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Kheda%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bench%20went%20on%20to%20underline%20that%20the%20accused%20cops%20%E2%80%9Chave%20defiled%20the%20human%20rights%20and%20dignity%20of%20the%20complainants%20as%20if%20they%20were%20conferred%20with%20the%20privilege%20to%20do%20so%E2%80%9D.%20The%20court%20said%20arrested%20persons%20also%20have%20the%20right%20to%20life%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20right%20to%20life%20with%20dignity%20and%20cannot%20be%20held%20back%20even%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHuman%20rights%20are%20not%20a%20privilege%20conferred%20by%20government%2C%20they%20are%20every%20human%20being%E2%80%99s%20entitlement%20by%20virtue%20of%20humanity.%20The%20right%20of%20life%20does%20not%20depend%20and%20must%20not%20be%20contingent%20on%20the%20pleasure%20of%20anyone%20else%2C%20not%20even%20a%20parent%20or%20a%20sovereign%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20quoted%20Mother%20Teresa.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20police%2C%20as%20custodians%20of%20law%20and%20order%2C%20the%20court%20said%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20not%20become%20depredations%20of%20civil%20liberties%20for%20their%20duty%20is%20to%20protect%20and%20not%20to%20abdicate%E2%80%9D.%20An%20accused%20person%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cdignity%20cannot%20be%20allowed%20to%20be%20comatose%E2%80%9D%20once%20the%20person%20is%20in%20police%20custody%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Supehia%20orally%20remarked%20that%20he%20never%20thought%20there%20would%20come%20a%20day%20when%20he%20had%20to%20order%20%E2%80%9Cpolice%20officers%20to%20undergo%20simple%20imprisonment%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20happy%E2%80%9D%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20policemen%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20Prakash%20Jani%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkheda-flogging-hitting-people-on-buttocks-with-stick-not-torture-cops-tell-gujarat-hc%5C%22%3Ehad%20told%20the%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20pronouncing%20them%20guilty%20and%20awarding%20them%20punishment%20would%20adversely%20affect%20their%20professional%20records%20given%20that%20they%20had%20already%20%E2%80%9Cdedicated%E2%80%9D%2010-15%20years%20to%20serve%20in%20the%20police%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkheda-flogging-hitting-people-on-buttocks-with-stick-not-torture-cops-tell-gujarat-hc%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20that%20one%20of%20the%20policemen%20had%20told%20the%20court%2C%20%E2%80%9CGiving%20three%20to%20six%20stick%20blows%20on%20buttocks%20of%20applicants%E2%80%A6%20though%20not%20proper%20and%20acceptable%2C%20it%20would%20not%20constitute%20custodial%20torture%20as%20to%20punish%20Respondent%20No%202%20(A.V.%20Parmar)%20for%20contempt%20of%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20victims%20had%20moved%20a%20petition%20before%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%20against%2015%20police%20personnel%20%E2%80%93%20the%20inspector%20general%20(IG)%2C%20the%20superintendent%20of%20police%20(SP)%2C%20Kheda%3B%2010%20constables%20from%20the%20Matar%20police%20station%3B%20and%20three%20officers%20from%20the%20local%20crime%20branch%20(LCB).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20had%20cited%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F235756%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ED.K.%20Basu%20versus%20the%20State%20of%20West%20Bengal%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Ecase%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20top%20court%20laid%20down%20basic%20%E2%80%9Crequirements%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20police%20to%20follow%20during%20arrest%20and%20detention%20until%20legal%20provisions%20are%20made%20%E2%80%93%20accusing%20the%20policemen%20of%20flouting%20norms.%20They%20had%20urged%20the%20court%20to%20initiate%20contempt%20of%20court%20proceedings%20against%20the%20policemen%20and%20also%20sought%20compensation%20be%20paid%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20videos%20of%20flogging%20which%20had%20gone%20viral%20on%20social%20media%20show%20accused%20policemen%20tying%20the%20victims%20to%20a%20poll%20and%20beating%20them%20with%20sticks%2C%20in%20full%20public%20view%20and%20amid%20cheers%20from%20the%20onlooking%20crowd.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697709637000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F05083127%2FScreenshot-2022-10-05-at-8.31.22-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkheda-public-flogging-gujarat-hc-awards-cops-14-day-jail-stays-verdict-for-3-months%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20police%2C%20as%20custodians%20of%20law%20and%20order%2C%20the%20court%20said%20'should%20not%20become%20depredations%20of%20civil%20liberties%20for%20their%20duty%20is%20to%20protect%20and%20not%20to%20abdicate'.%20An%20accused%20person's%20'dignity%20cannot%20be%20allowed%20to%20be%20comatose'%20once%20the%20person%20is%20in%20police%20custody%2C%20it%20added.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkheda-public-flogging-gujarat-hc-awards-cops-14-day-jail-stays-verdict-for-3-months%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Citibank%20gets%20court%20relief%20after%20sacking%20worker%20over%20two-sandwich%20lunch%20claim%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697709499000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104552701%2Cimgsize-52440.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fcitibank-gets-court-relief-after-sacking-worker-over-two-sandwich-lunch-claim%2Farticleshow%2F104552723.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104552723.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EA%20former%20Citibank%20worker%20in%20the%20UK%20was%20sacked%20after%20claiming%20reimbursement%20for%20meals%20he%20shared%20with%20his%20partner%20during%20a%20work%20trip%20to%20Amsterdam.%20The%20worker%20initially%20lied%20about%20consuming%20the%20food%20and%20drinks%20himself%2C%20