are%20the%20buoys%20in%20the%20sea.%20Made%20from%20fibre%20which%20is%20anti-corrosive%2C%20these%20buoys%C2%A0are%20being%20replaced%20by%20plastic%20ones%20these%20days%20by%20fishermen%20and%20are%20being%20discarded%20carelessly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENaomi%20and%20Yohann%20then%20buy%20them%20from%20the%20fishermen%20to%20make%20planters%20embellished%20with%20mosaic%20or%20to%20build%20lotus%20ponds%20in%20which%20you%20can%20also%20put%20fish.%20The%20fibre%20is%20cleaned%2C%20refurbished%20and%20reused%20to%20make%20the%20signature%20planters%20or%20pond%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20adhere%20to%20our%20eco-friendly%20practices%20of%20minimum%20usage%20of%20chemicals%20on%20the%20wood.%20This%20way%2C%20it%20retains%20its%20natural%20beauty%20as%20well.%20We%20use%20linseed%20oil%20and%20tung%20oil%20as%20curing%20agents%20for%20protecting%20the%20wood%20and%20giving%20it%20a%20finish.%20However%2C%20we%20have%20to%20use%20an%20anti-termite%20solution%20to%20ensure%20the%20products%20are%20long-lasting.%20Otherwise%2C%20there%20is%20no%20point%20talking%20of%20sustainability%20if%20the%20products%20won%E2%80%99t%20last%20for%20the%20customer.%20We%20use%20machines%20to%20cut%20the%20wood%20but%20our%20products%20are%20hand%20polished%2C%E2%80%9D%20elaborates%20Yohann.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20wastage%20in%20the%20studio%20is%20kept%20to%20a%20minimum.%20Naomi%20collects%20the%20pieces%20that%20are%20left%20over%20from%20her%20pieces%20in%20three%20containers%20depending%20on%20their%20size%20and%20reuses%20them.%20Only%20the%20fine%20tile%20powder%20is%20wasted.%20Even%20in%20wood%20materials%2C%20wastage%20is%20avoided.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20big%20piece%20of%20driftwood%20is%20cut%20into%20two%20so%20that%20one%20piece%20can%20be%20used%20to%20make%20a%20lamp%20and%20the%20other%20a%20side%20table.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20458px)%20100